workflow.name: Automatically sync Notion contacts to Google Contacts with group labels
workflow.description:
## Sync Notion Contacts to Google Contacts with Group Labels


**Overview**  
Seamlessly transfer your Notion contacts to Google Contacts with organized group labels, simplifying your CRM management.

This n8n workflow automates syncing contacts from a Notion database to Google Contacts, applying group labels based on Notion properties. It triggers on new or updated contacts, ensuring your Google Contacts are always organized without manual effort.

‚ú® **Key Features**  
üîÑ **Automatic Sync:** Updates Google Contacts when Notion entries are added or modified.  
üè∑Ô∏è **Group Organization:** Assigns labels to contacts based on Notion‚Äôs `property_buy` field.  
‚úÖ **Duplicate Prevention:** Marks synced contacts in Notion with a checkbox.  
üõ†Ô∏è **Flexible Customization:** Add fields like email in the ‚ÄúMap Notion Contact Fields‚Äù node.  
üì° **Community Nodes:** Leverages Notion and Google Contacts nodes for integration.

üìã **Prerequisites**  
**Required Credentials**  
- **Notion API Token:** Set up OAuth2 in n8n. Get your token from [Notion‚Äôs API settings](https://developers.notion.com/).  
- **Google Contacts OAuth2:** Configure in n8n. See [n8n‚Äôs Google Contacts guide](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/credentials/google/).  
- **Notion Database:** Must include name, phone, labels (`property_buy`), and an ‚ÄúAdded to Contacts‚Äù checkbox.  
- **Self-Hosted n8n:** Required for community nodes.

üîÑ **Workflow Process**  
1. **Trigger:** Activates on new or updated Notion database entries.  
2. **Fetch Data:** Retrieves contact details (name, phone, labels) from Notion.  
3. **Map Fields:** Organizes data in the ‚ÄúMap Notion Contact Fields‚Äù node.  
4. **Verify Groups:** Checks for existing Google Contact groups; creates new ones if needed.  
5. **Sync Contacts:** Adds contacts to Google Contacts with labels.  
6. **Update Notion:** Marks contacts as synced.  
**Result:** Organized, labeled contacts in Google Contacts, updated automatically.

üìä **Output Data Structure**  
- **Name:** Contact‚Äôs first name from Notion.  
- **Phone:** Contact‚Äôs phone number.  
- **Group Labels:** Assigned from Notion‚Äôs `property_buy` field.  
- **Sync Status:** Notion checkbox updated to confirm sync.

üí° **Pro Tips**  
- **Real-Time Updates:** Set the Notion Trigger node to check every minute for faster syncing.  
- **Expand Fields:** Add email or other fields in the ‚ÄúMap Notion Contact Fields‚Äù node.  
- **Clean Labels:** Use consistent Notion labels for better Google Contacts organization.  
- **Test Small:** Start with a small dataset to verify setup.

üÜò **Troubleshooting**  
- **Authentication Issues:** Verify Notion and Google Contacts OAuth2 credentials.  
- **Sync Failures:** Ensure Notion database ID and field names match the workflow.  
- **Group Errors:** Check that `property_buy` labels are valid.  

üë®‚Äçüíª **Creator Information**

ü§ù **Support & Contributions**

parameters.content:
# Sync Notion Contacts to Google Contacts with Group Labels
This workflow syncs contacts from a Notion database to Google Contacts, assigning group labels based on Notion properties. It triggers on new or updated contacts, retrieves details (name, phone, labels), checks/creates Google Contact groups, adds the contact, and updates Notion to mark it as synced.

**Setup Instructions:**
1. Connect Notion and Google Contacts via OAuth2 in n8n‚Äôs credential settings.
2. Set your Notion database ID in the Notion Trigger node (find it in your Notion database URL, e.g., 0427eb01ed3b4947873382c566f23785).
3. Ensure Notion database has fields: name, phone, labels, and ‚ÄúAdded to Contacts‚Äù checkbox.
4. Test the workflow to confirm syncing.

**Requirements:**
- Notion account with a contact database.
- Google Contacts account with OAuth2.
- **Self-hosted n8n instance required (uses community nodes).**

For advanced setups, see [Notion‚Äôs API guide](https://developers.notion.com/).
Triggers the workflow when a new contact is added or an existing contact is updated in the specified Notion database.
Maps Notion fields (name, phone, labels, added status) to variables for further processing. Customize here to add more fields like email.
Matches Notion labels to existing Google Contact groups, parsing labels from Notion‚Äôs property_buy field.
Checks if the contact has already been synced to Google Contacts using the 'Already Added' field in Notion.
Verifies if the specified group label exists in Google Contacts. If not, a new group is created.
Creates a new group in Google Contacts if the specified label doesn‚Äôt exist.
Adds the contact to Google Contacts with the specified name, phone, and group labels.

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
